<h1 align="CENTER">ICR Yellowstone Tour</h1>
<h2 align="CENTER">September 8-16, 2000</h2>



The <a data-original-url="http://www.icr.org" data-wayback-date="" href="http://www.icr.org">Institute for Creation Research</a> will be leading a tour of Yellowstone and Grand Tetons National Parks, Fossil Butte, Ulrich's Fossil Gallery, and Dinosaur National Monument.  The tour will be led by Steven A. Austin, Ph.D. (geology), Rolland Kuhr, M.S. (forestry), David Nutting, M.S. (geology), Frank Sherwin, M..A. (zoology), Larry Vardeman, Ph.D. (meteorology), and Tom Manning.  The cost is $1245 per person, and includes luxury touring coach, first-class motels (double occupancy), admission to all parks and attractions, instruction, and two guide books.  There is a $50 discount if you pay before July 1, 2000.

<p>Dave Pogge took this tour in September, 1996, and found it well worth the price.

</p><p>For more information, contact ICR directly at P.O. Box 2667, El Cajon, CA 92021.  Their phone number is 619-596-6034.



